	<Title>
		Protein: Heart-healthy sources
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Does your diet include unhealthy sources of protein, perhaps burgers, hot dogs and fried chicken in excess? Do your heart a favor and choose your proteins wisely. Legumes are a great source of heart-healthy protein. They include beans, peas and lentils. Legumes are typically low in fat and contain no cholesterol. They&apos;re also rich in folate, potassium, iron and magnesium. Legumes also contain beneficial fats and soluble and insoluble fiber.&lt;/p&gt;
